{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"19fdf6ea-01c0-4e37-b083-15c9b8d6da5a","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Blocked by bug #123\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four will report the test as **skipped/ignored** (not failed) in test results, with your reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6a879098-004d-4538-81c6-5db341650f40","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":305,"requestId":"1BD9:3969BE:6CAE4BB:752EBE5:6A03D24C"},"id":"7e54ef00-d095-44c3-8c7e-763c942fae5a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:22:28.051Z","parentId":"80098c72-a9c1-4c52-a4cb-279a7a9bc39f"}
